column2: 32,000 people, and hundreds more by the minute, since this morning are getting protected by the free COVID-19 coverage and Personal Accident Insurance. Your patience is much appreciated as the system adjusts to this enthusiastic response.   Here are some helpful tips for a great experience with Pulse: 1. Please make sure you have a good internet connection. 2. Don't forget to nominate your beneficiary when you get to the Congratulatory screen. In case you were not able to nom...inate a beneficiary, please expect the 'Add Beneficiary' feature in 7 days or less. 3. In case your ID number and/or name is not captured well by the camera, you can manually input it, but please avoid hyphens or other special symbols. 4. Make sure to double check your birthdate as sometimes the system defaults to 2019 as the year. Do stay tuned to PULSE as we continue to release more updates. Click here to download Pulse for Android or iOS: https://wedopulseph.page.link/vwyH

Through our AI-powered chatbot, you can input your symptoms and answer related questions so that your condition can be better analyzed. This will help you understand your symptom better. Download it now for FREE: https://wedopulseph.page.link/5dT1

column2: In observance of the Holy Week, our business will be closed from April 9 to 10. Normal operations will resume on Monday, April 13. You may manage your policy through PRUAccess at https://pruaccess.prulifeuk.com.ph.

[UPDATE] Because we heard you! Due to some of your concerns on downloading Pru Life UK‚Äôs health app, Pulse, the launch date of the FREE COVID-19 insurance & personal accident coverage will be moved to April 13. Those who have downloaded the app will receive an in-app notification, so don‚Äôt forget to log in to your account! ---- Starting April 11, leading life insurer Pru Life UK will offer free COVID-19 protection and Personal Accident (PA) coverage to safeguard Filipinos amid the coronavirus outbreak in the country. Under the program, Pru Life UK will offer free accident and death benefit to 500,000 Filipinos, in the unfortunate event that the individual passes away, including as a result of COVID-19. Health workers are entitled to twice the death coverage at no cost. This offer is available through Pulse, Pru Life UK‚Äôs artificial intelligence-powered health and wellness app that offers holistic health management.  Click link to read full story. #WeDoHealth

column2: What is the Pulse Healthcheck? Healthcheck will help you know yourself better by answering a series of questions. Afterwards, a 3D view of your body will be generated based on your answers. You can now visualize your health with your very own DIGITAL TWIN and help you discover detailed insights into your current health and also help you improve your lifestyle. Learn more about yourself. Download Pulse now for FREE on Google Play Store or Apple App Store: https://wedopulseph.page.link/5dT1

column2: Due to local government guidelines to manage the COVID-19 health emergency across the country, our business centers in Iloilo and Tacloban are temporarily close...d until further notice. In addition, our Davao business centers will also cease operations effective Thursday, March 26. Offices in Luzon will remain closed. Our live customer service will not be available until further notice. Customers may reach out to their financial advisors for any concern on their policies. Alternatively, customers may review and manage their policies through customer portal PRUAccess at https://pruaccess.prulifeuk.com.ph/ or email PRU Customer Action Team at contact.us@prulifeuk.com.ph. We continue to assess and release more timely announcements as the local authorities implement further measures and guidelines.
